# Prototype Trend Sparklines From Edition History

## Step

Tufte small multiples from `data/editions/*.json` — the history already exists, nothing new to collect. Candidates: observations per source over time (is gmail quiet? is github spiking?), open-loop count and age distribution across editions, shipped-vs-open trajectory once loop closure lands. Deterministic inline SVG, word-sized where it earns it — a true sparkline inside a sentence beats a chart block.

The taste bar: informative, not decorative. Every sparkline must answer a question Joel would actually ask; anything that's just "data being visible" gets cut.

Resolved when the masthead or an edition section carries at least one sparkline Joel finds informative rather than decorative.
